[2]
Date: 11 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health 11 Apr 2003 [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 11 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 1 PM 11 Apr 2003, an additional 61 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 11 healthcare
workers (5 from Princess Margaret Hospital, 2 from Alice Ho Miu Ling
Nethersole Hospital, one from North District Hospital, and one from Hong
Kong Baptist Hospital) and 11 patients from Amoy Gardens. The remaining 39
were new patients and contacts of patients with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 169 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 15 were discharged
today. Most of the patients currently in hospital are showing positive
responses to the new treatment protocol. 121 patients are receiving
treatment in intensive care unit.
2 patients died in hospitals, bring to 32 the total number of deaths
related to atypical pneumonia. A 81-year-old male with a history of chronic
disease died in Prince of Wales Hospital last night and a 79-year-old male
patient died in United Christian Hospital this morning.
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Cumulative no. cases/ total no. discharged/ total no. deaths
(all reported cases had signs of pneumonia)
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students: 264/ 78 32
Patients, family members & visitors: 795/ 91
Total: 1059/ 169
* Most of the deaths occurred in individuals who have a history of
chronic diseases, or were patients who sought treatment at a relatively
late stage of infection.
--
