Source: Taiwan - Center for Disease Control Taiwan [edited]
<http://203.65.72.83/En/dpc/ShowPublication.ASP?RecNo=852>

Taiwan SARS Updated on 11 Apr 2003
1. As of 15:00 PM on 11 Apr 2003, there were 147 possible SARS cases
reported. They include 23 probable, 37 suspected, 72 excluded, and 15
pending cases. In accordance with WHO guidelines, 7 of the probable and 15
of the suspected cases were discharged to home quarantine while the other
16 probable and 22 suspected cases are still being cared for in negative
pressure rooms. A total of 60 possible SARS cases have been discharged from
hospitals.
2. As of 11 Apr 2003, local health stations distributed SARS home
quarantine notifications to 1458 persons who had close contact with
probable SARS cases. 988 of them have been relieved of the quarantine order.
3. Since SARS is a new emerging infectious disease and its cause agent has
not been confirmed, a probable case is identified based on epidemiologic
data, clinical data, laboratory diagnosis data, and further serology is
needed to confirm the diagnosis. Taiwan SARS Advisory Committee did not
recommend the early release of the results of coronavirus test by RT-PCR to
the local health authorities for their reference. Taiwan CDC advises the
local health authorities to take precautionary measures as soon as they
receive a reported SARS case, without laboratory diagnosis.
--
